---
// Homepage self-introduction, written from the owner's CV (2026-04).
// Prose-only block — rendered inside Hero, directly under the slogan.
import type { Locale } from '~/i18n/config'

interface Props {
  locale: Locale
}

const { locale } = Astro.props

const SCHOLAR = 'https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=nyGUv2kAAAAJ&hl=en'
---

<div
  class="intro-prose mx-auto max-w-[44rem] space-y-5 text-left font-serif text-copy-15 leading-loose text-neutral-8 lg:text-copy-16"
>
  {
    locale === 'en' ? (
      <>
        <p>
          I am a postdoctoral researcher (Shuimu Scholar) at Tsinghua
          University's School of Public Policy and Management, working
          with Prof. Tang Xiao. I previously interned at MiniMax, working
          on post-training data algorithms — a spell of amphibious life
          between academia and the AI industry. Before this I earned my
          PhD in public administration at Shanghai Jiao Tong University
          under Prof. Chen Jie, after studying land resource management
          at Nanjing University and real estate at Central China Normal
          University.
        </p>
        <p>
          I'm drawn to whatever research is interesting. I like answering
          questions with survey experiments, causal inference, and lately
          LLM-agent simulations — how the rise and fall of housing prices
          shapes ordinary people's political trust, whether victories on
          the Olympic field convert into a "political dividend", and
          whether AI agents can stand in for human subjects in behavioral
          experiments. This work has appeared in <em>The China Quarterly</em>,{' '}
          <em>Policy Sciences</em>, <em>Chinese Political Science Review</em>{' '}
          and elsewhere. A full publication list lives on{' '}
          <a href={SCHOLAR} rel="noreferrer" target="_blank">
            Google Scholar
          </a>
          .
        </p>
        <p>
          Outside research, I run the WeChat account
          「人类有趣行为实验室」 (Human Intriguing Behavior Lab), where I
          unpack important and interesting economics papers and share AI
          tools and techniques. This blog shelters the rest of my writing:
          research notes, essays on daily life, and murmurs that refuse to
          be lost.
        </p>
        <p>
          If any of this interests you, feel free to reach me through any
          of the icons below.
        </p>
      </>
    ) : (
      <>
        <p>
          我目前在清华大学公共管理学院做博士后研究（助理研究员、水木学者），合作导师是唐啸老师；曾经在
          MiniMax 实习，做后训练数据算法——在学术界与 AI
          业界之间过了一段两栖生活。在此之前，我在上海交通大学取得公共管理博士学位（师从陈杰教授），更早则在南京大学读土地资源管理、在华中师范大学读房地产开发与管理。
        </p>
        <p>
          我关注有趣的研究，习惯用调查实验、因果推断，以及最近的大模型智能体模拟来回答问题——房价的涨落如何塑造普通人的政治信任？奥运赛场上的胜利能否转化为「政治红利」？AI
          智能体能不能替人类受试者完成行为实验？相关工作发表在{' '}
          <em>The China Quarterly</em>、<em>Policy Sciences</em>、
          <em>Chinese Political Science Review</em>{' '}
          等期刊，完整的论文列表在{' '}
          <a href={SCHOLAR} rel="noreferrer" target="_blank">
            Google Scholar
          </a>
          。
        </p>
        <p>
          研究之外，我运营公众号「人类有趣行为实验室」，解读重要而有趣的经济学论文，也分享
          AI
          技术与工具。这个博客则收留更多样的文字：研究笔记、生活随笔，以及一些不愿散佚的呓语。
        </p>
        <p>如果你对这些话题感兴趣，欢迎通过下方的任意图标找到我。</p>
      </>
    )
  }
</div>

<style>
  .intro-prose a {
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
    text-decoration-color: color-mix(in oklab, currentColor 30%, transparent);
    transition: text-decoration-color 0.2s;
  }
  .intro-prose a:hover {
    text-decoration-color: currentColor;
  }
</style>
